commentary: I Sharma to Finch, OUT given! What a delivery that is. Ducks back in prodigiously to hit Finch outside the line of off stump. But he wasn't offering a stroke. Umpire Kettleborough had no hesitation and raised his finger immediately but did that nip back in enough? Lots of swing for Ishant, the first time we have seen as much in this series.

commentary: Gurkeerat Singh to Warner, 1 run, OUT Marsh may be gone. This will be a huge wicket. marsh is gone. What a fortunate dismissal that is for India. Short outside off, Warner crashes a cut to deep point. And calls Marsh through. The throw is not very good, bounces just in front of Gurkeerat. The ball hits the knee of Gurkeerat and then ricochets onto the stumps to find Marsh short. Could be a massive moment in this game

Takes the first run quickly, and he completes the second comfortably enough to break into his usual leaping century celebration. This has been another excellent innings. He's paced it so well and Australia are in a very good position despite those wickets lost

Dhawan has thrown away a really really good start

commentary: MR Marsh to Pandey, 1 run slower short ball outside off, wide of Pandey who's moved across his stumps. Chopped down towards backward point
text: slower short ball outside off, wide of Pandey who's moved across his stumps. Chopped down towards backward point

commentary: MR Marsh to Dhoni, 2 runs down the track and he  gets too close to this ball from Marsh. Jabs it down towards long-off, and the electric Pandey turns quickly to complete the second, but a direct hit would have done for him

commentary: MR Marsh to Dhoni, FOUR runs full and wide and this time Dhoni is right where he needs to be. Huge backlift, flat-bats it down the ground, absolutely smashes it and long-off has no chance going to his right

commentary: MR Marsh to Dhoni, 1 run full outside off, slower ball. Dhoni slogs and inside-edges towards short fine leg

commentary: Faulkner to Dhoni, 1 run full on middle and leg, clips to midwicket, who's slightly deep and allows a reasonably comfortable single

commentary: Faulkner to Pandey, 1 run down the track, looks to make room. Faulkner denies him the room with the slower ball and he slogs it out to deep midwicket, on the bounce

commentary: Faulkner to Dhoni, 2 runs full-toss on leg stump, Dhoni lap-sweeps towards long leg
text: full-toss on leg stump, Dhoni lap-sweeps towards long leg

commentary: Faulkner to Dhoni, 1 leg bye sees him making room and follows him. Slogs at it, misses, and it ricochets off the pad into the off side

commentary: Faulkner to Pandey, 2 runs down the track and Pandey is an absolute genius at landing the ball short of deep fielders. Takes his bottom hand off the handle while chasing the full, wide slower ball, and it drops short of the sweeper cover fielder running to his right

commentary: Faulkner to Pandey, 2 runs down the track, Faulkner follows him, and he tucks it away through backward square leg and picks up two, leaving Dhoni at strike at the start of the last over

commentary: MR Marsh to Dhoni, 1 wide full and wide, and it's given wide after Dhoni leaves it alone. Harsh call, seemed to be just inside the tramline, though, as Wasim Akram reminds us on TV commentary - the line is just an indication

commentary: MR Marsh to Dhoni, SIX runs bam! That's a low full-toss outside off, in Dhoni's slot, but in this innings he hasn't been middling anything. He doesn't middle this either, but he just about clears the leaping long-off fielder. Warner is the fielder. He would have needed to be as tall as Mohammad Irfan to take that

commentary: MR Marsh to Dhoni, OUT full and wide and Dhoni goes after it and holes out, Warner takes a simple catch running in from long-off. They cross over, however, and Pandey will be on strike
text: full and wide and Dhoni goes after it and holes out, Warner takes a simple catch running in from long-off. They cross over, however, and Pandey will be on strike

commentary: MR Marsh to Pandey, FOUR runs shot. That's full outside off, a wide yorker, almost, and Pandey, cool as a cucumber, brings up his hundred in style. Lets it come on, opens his bat face at impact, and steers it fine to the third man boundary. This has been an outstanding one-day innings

commentary: MR Marsh to Pandey, 2 runs and it's all over. Full outside off and Pandey launches this over the covers. Doesn't really middle it, but all he needs to do is clear the infield, and that's what he does
